DIGITAL creator and skit maker, Godson Chukwuebuka Eze aka Agent of laughter has opened up on his choice of moniker and what it means to him.   AVRS, NCC meet stakeholders in Lagos     All eyes are on Nigeria, we must do better, says Sleek     The Ibeji Live Experience returns to Terra Kulture on July…   The comedy merchant disclosed this to The Nation in a recent chat saying, “When I was trying to come up with the name, I did some deep thinking, and then I felt like okay how do I tell people that laughter is my priority. So, ‘Agent of laughter’ simply means laughter has sent me”, he noted. Speaking on his journey into comedy and skit-making, the Imo State-born said, “I started my comedy career when I entered the university. That was during my first year but I was not so serious about it then, doing it just for hobby’s sake. The first opportunity I had to feature in a big comedy skit was with the Xploit comedy team then followed by Brodashaggi. Then afterward, the little exposure I had after this experience made me take the job seriously because I wanted exposure and the famous lifestyle.”